===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|lynspin}}, compound of {{m|enm|lins|t=axletree}} and {{m|enm|pin}}, from {{der|en|ang|lynis|t=lynchpin}}, from {{der|en|gem-pro|*lunaz}} – compare {{cog|de|Lünse}} and {{cog|nl|luns}} – from {{der|en|ine-pro|-}}. Possible further cognates are {{cog|cy|olwyn|t=wheel}}, {{cog|xcl|ողն|t=back; spine, backbone}} and {{cog|sa|आणि|t=lynchpin|tr=āṇí}}. Figurative use attested from the mid-20th century.

