# {{lb|en|figuratively}} A central [[cohesive]] source of [[stability]] and [[security]]; a person or thing that is critical to a system or organisation.
#* {{quote-journal|en|magazine=The Eastern Economist|year=1958|passage=What is difficult to appreciate, however, is the discrepancy between his statement to the 'Manchester Guardian' correspondent and his known abhorance for party politics, which is the '''lynchpin''' of modern democracy.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|title=Community and Public Health Nursing|page=2006|author=Dvaid Sines|year=2013|passage=Community nurses have been described as the '''lynchpins''' of palliative care in the community.}}

